ke this. But when they repent, the GMs should allow a random on the item. IMHO.<br><br>A funny side note - after this hopeless shouting match with the Bard, I go back to get the claw I had won. It's gone. I ask who looted it. The mage says, with sarcassm, "Guess who? :-P". The Bard says, and I quote, "I have it. Should we roll on it?". We all manage a laugh. I tell him, "Gee, I think I won that roll already.". He hands me the claw; Im sure he was well-pleased.<br><br>A thief, a fool, or both? Or simply The Ninja?<br><br>Ah well, perhaps karma will drop a Forest Loop on me, when I make the jump to Frontier Mountains...<br><br>Arynduil Greyleaf<br>28th Ranger of Tunare<br>Erollsi Marr<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Arynduil<br>Hunter, EMarr<br><br>"In a crowded Universe, when the talking turns to noise, you almost start laughing"</td></td></tr>
